						</button>
						<div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-2">
							<p>Yes, GEO complements SEO and AEO to create comprehensive search visibility. Millions of users now use ChatGPT, Claude, and Gemini as their primary search interface. These systems generate responses by learning from web content. If your content isn't optimized for generative AI discovery and understanding, you're invisible to this growing user base. SEO, AEO, and GEO work together to provide complete search visibility across all search types.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-3">
							<span>What platforms does GEO optimize for?</span>
							<span class="faq-icon">+</span>
						</button>
						<div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-3">
							<p>GEO optimizes for generative AI systems including ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity, and AI agents. The goal is to ensure your content is discovered, learned from, and cited when these systems generate responses to user queries. GEO also prepares your content for future generative AI platforms as they emerge.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-4">
							<span>How long does it take to see GEO results?</span>
							<span class="faq-icon">+</span>
						</button>
						<div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-4">
							<p>GEO results can take longer than SEO or AEO because generative AI systems need to learn from your content and include it in their knowledge bases. You may start seeing your content cited in generative AI responses within 3-6 months, though this varies based on your industry, competition, content quality, and how frequently AI systems update their knowledge bases.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-5">
							<span>What content works best for GEO?</span>
							<span class="faq-icon">+</span>
